text: Biryubash () is a rural locality (a village) in Novotroitsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 378 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 26 km from Mishkino, 7 km from Novotroitskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Biryubash
